\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Mesopotamians recognized enki as the god who brings civilization to humankind. It is he who gives rulers their intelligence and knowledge; he opens the doors of understanding; teaches humans how to construct canals and plan temples, putting their foundation pegs in exactly the right places; he brings forth abundance in the waters; not the ruler of the universe but the gods wise counsellor and elder brother; he is lord of the assembly; he is nudimmud, the shaper, the fashioner of images, the patron of artisans and craftsmen. It was he who divided the speech of mankind. }
